Yaana - Siddharth's Linux IPC infrastructure
======

Yaana (work in progress) is an effort to create an efficient & reliable IPC mechanism through which linux processes can talk to each other.

############
# Check Pre-requisites
############

1> You must have the Linux Module source (linux-headers) for your distribution.

	ls /lib/modules/$(shell uname -r)/build -la 

   should give an output. This ensures that the module can be compiled on your Linux. 

#############
# INSTALL
#############

./run.sh

############
# Check installation 
############

Check if the module has been installed using

	lsmod | grep "yaana"

#############
# UNINSTALL
#############

./uninstall.sh
